ny other god would have been driven insane LONG ago probably within moments of taking on this responsibility.  He endured.  But even his mind bordered the edge of sanity.  He stood up and walked about his throne room.  He then melded with a shadow and vanished from the room.<br>
     Hades found himself now standing on the Elysian fields.  This always seemed to be a much happier place.  Heroes and just generally kind hearted people wandered this place.  Even Lord Hades had to crack a slight smile in a place like this.  People were happy here.  And those who chose to leave and return to life had the choice to do so after a while, to reincarnate.  <br>
     Hades then remembered something he had long forgotten.  Yes, he could learn more than most from the Dead.  All who entered his realm, he learned from.  Learned their secrets and their knowledges.  But knowing the secrets of Death was only half of everything.  To truley understand things, one also had to have an understanding as to how Life worked.  And with that thought, Hades vanished.  He appeared somewhere in the realms of Greece, in the guise of an unknown wanderer.  For months he wandered the Greek countryside and cities.  Every so often changing his form, to avoid being &quot;recognized&quot;.  He even guised as one of his own priests for a while.::<br>
